intel_cards.summary:
Two separate air defence failures let missiles get through, Israeli military says&nbsp;






                Israeli military spokesperson Brig. Gen. Effie Defrin said interceptors were launched in both cases of Iranian missile fire on Saturday but failed to stop the incoming attack.

More than 90% of launches are typically intercepted, he added.&nbsp;

The two Iranian missiles injured more than 150 people in southern Israel on Saturday, hospital officials say.

Seven Israeli soldiers wounded in southern Lebanon: Report






                Four Israeli soldiers have been lightly injured during a “safety incident” while operating in southern Lebanon, Al Jazeera is reporting, citing Israel’s Walla news outlet.&nbsp;

Additionally, another soldier was lightly wounded following a drone strike near a military unit in the same area.

